content.description:
Start on the slab to the left of the vertical crack/gully.  Climb up the right trending ramp to clip the first bolt.  Continue up the slab to the roof, climb over the roof and finish on easy climbing to the top.  Same anchor as Where's My Brush.



At the slabs, After Hours is the route farthest left when at the bottom facing the crag.  There is an obvious vertical crack/gully, After Hours route is to the left of the crack.


7 Bolts, Quick clips.

Follow bolts up the dark streak with a prominent triangular bulge about two thirds the way up. 
 A great first lead for a beginning leader.

In the quarry
9 bolts + Rap rings

Climb up the obvious hand/fist crack at the left end of the cliff. As it trends around the corner, 
 follow the crack up the slab and left of a couple small trees (cedar & birch). Step right of the dirt 
 ledge, following easy moves up a rounded arete to ring anchors.

The obvious handcrack on the left side of the cliff. Divides the slabs with the rest of the quarry.
Standard rack. Rap rings

climbs.name: Crazy Yahoos shooting shit
climbs.fa: FFA: L. Gallant, D. Caron, M. Thériault

content.description:
Face climb the first few bolts heading for the 'funny angle overhang'. At the overhang follow the horizontal seam smearing your feet and pull the lip on the left by doing a combination of crimping and laybacking. To the left of Yodeling Yak and to the right of Torpedoes and Jellyfish. The 2nd bolted route right of the obvious hand crack 'Chubby girls wearing shower curtains' 9 bolts, well protected
Shared Maillon anchor

climbs.name: Domino Effect
climbs.fa: Ian Lingley, Josh Shewbridge, Eric Samis

content.description:
start over a small bulge and work up the open book corner, then through a few small roofs to join in the top section of "Gomez, Lopez, Fitzgerald".  

start about 10' left of "Gomez, Lopez, Fitzgerald".
10 bolts, quick clips.

Start on a sequency 4 bolt overhang. After the 4th bolt move left on some face moves and head for a massive undercling. Crank over the undercling and head straight to the anchor clipping. The route name is according to a friend: ''the 3 most common Mexican names''. Pumpy route. To the left of the obvious arête Macguffin in the huge open book with black hangers. 9 bolts. A couple of long quickdraws are useful as this route wanders a bit.
Lower-off anchor

climbs.name: Happy Birthday to Me
climbs.fa: Cory Goodman, Adam Morgan, & Anders Fougner

content.description:
This line ascends a brief vertical face for 2 bolts before launching into a low angle slab full of trees and funky solution features. At one point, there is a mono-sized wormhole in the stone. Can you find it?

From the main quarry walk downhill past and ancient retaining wall and loop back right towards the slabs. First route encountered. The rap station at the top is approachable on foot and as such serves as a good approach/retreat route.
2 bolts and a light rack

climbs.name: La mére à Luc pis des burritos
climbs.fa: FFA: M. Thériault, L. Gallant, D. Caron

content.description:
Climb easy ledges leading you to a crux up top. Left of Tequila and Limestone. Two routes right from Macguffin, the obvious arête. bolts
Same anchor as Yousqué ta cell

This route is the obvious prominent arête. Start on some funky blocky features powering delicately through the technical crux of the route. Once on the arête, fight the pump to the anchors.

On the obvious arête, left of Tequila and Limestone
12 bolts. A 0.4 or 0.5 BD size cam could be useful to avoid having to clip the awkward 11th bolt.

Stick clip the first bolt, one move will get you to a nice jug. Climb the weirdly featured face past the second bolt. Clip the third bolt from the right side, and then pull over the top. Shares an anchor with Tor-Til-Ah. This a 3 bolt sport climb located on a ledge in the very back of the quarry. 3 bolts 2 raprings
stick clip first bolt

Work your way up a delicate set of moves on an interesting bulge. A thought-provoking, enjoyable climb.

1st bolt line adjacent and left to the bolted corner system (Schmucks Unlimited)
9 bolts to bolted anchor

climbs.name: Schmucks Unlimited
climbs.fa: C. Goodman, Burly, Beurkle, jones, morgan  (FFA C.goodman, G.mackenney)

content.description:
This climb starts in the back corner of the quarry and is the most popular rap line into the quarry. Start from the flat ledge with a few cedars on it, climb up the corner behind the cedar tree. Nice ledges with good hand holds will help move up the corner, when the corner ends the climb goes a little left. After clipping the last bolt the climb follows the beautiful crack up the head wall to the anchor.

main quarry, back coner.
Sport, 15' from last bolt to anchor with Cam option

climbs.name: Shaved Bird
climbs.fa: FA: C Goodman, P Arsenault, (FFA: C Goodman, D Caron, L Gallant)

content.description:
Same start as Poop Deck, but at the second bolt, trend slightly right to climb the seemingly blank rock below triangular roof once on the ledge follow the bolts to the more natural looking rock towards the top. Finish at the Schmucks Unlimited anchor.

In the back coner of the quarry just left of schmucks unlimited
sport 7 bolts 2 raprings

Begin 15 feet left of Chica Bonita and go up a series of small ledges and smaller roofs. (Maillon 
 anchors courtesy of E Burley.) 
 Note: Dominic led the FFA in the fog, after dark, without a headlamp, and before placing the 4 
 lowest bolts.

in the Quarry, left of Chica Bonita
10 bolts and Quick-clip anchor

climbs.name: Theme night
climbs.fa: C Goodman, Z Levesque & D Caron

content.description:
This is a (nicer?) variation of Chubby Girls Wearing Shower Curtains. Instead of following the 
 main crack onto the slab, continue straight upward through steeper terrain followed by thinner 
 features right of the small trees. Clip one of the Chubby Girls... anchors and continue up and 
 right to link up with the finish of Torpedoes and Jellyfish.

Start on the obvious Chubby girls handcrack
3 bolts. Standard rack

climbs.name: Theme Night  Direct
climbs.fa: FFA Corey G, Dom C, Z Levesque

content.description:
This is a great natural limestone route. Start in the same little corner as Chubby Girls, climb up under the angled roof moving right, youll get a bomb undercling. Moving up and slightly left of the under cling you will find beautiful features leading you to a corner with a bolt. Climb the corner the second bolt is part of chubby girls... anchor once you clip the bolt the route move right across extraordinary water groves crosses 1 or 2 more bolts to rap rings.


just right of "Chubby Girls.."

This route take great gear, some placements are a little funky because its lime stone.

This route starts just right of a cut cedar growing out of the cliff near the base, and follows the 
 series of bolts through a gentle overhang of dark rock. Continue up the crack beyond the 6th bolt 
 and follow it as it branches right to shared maillon anchor.

First bolted route to the right of the obvious 15' hand crack found on the left end of the crag.
8 bolts + maillon anchor

Climb up the cruxy slabby start and then enjoy the huge pockets to the top. This route can be used to climb out or rappel in. Follow the trail through the trees behind Crazy Yahoos Shooting Shit and down the granite blocks
before looping back to the base of the limestone retaining wall. You will encounter two routes here. This is the one on the right. Happy Birthday to me 5.8 is the one on the left. 8 bolts.
A tree can be slung in the middle of the route.
Maillon anchor

Follow the water-eroded features to a few short cracks. After the solitary bolt, stay close to the 
 trees and look for more gear placements before climbing the rounded arete to the ring anchors 
 shared with Chubby Girls Wearing Shower Curtains.

Follow the trail along base of the cliff until it ends abruptly atop a 10 limestone retaining wall.
1 bolts, standard rack

Start to the right of the vertical crack/gully.  Climb up the face and clip the first bolt.  Continue climbing up the face (not the crack/gully) to the second bolt.  Continue climbing up through the small roof then on easier terrain to the top. Don't let the name prevent you from climbing the route (brush not required).



At the slabs there are two original routes from 2009 (Happy Birthday to Me and Walk the Plank).  Where's My Brush is to the left of walk the plank.  There is an obvious vertical crack/gully at the bottom near the route.  Where's My Brush is to the right of this vertical crack/gully.

7 Bolts, Quickshots

Crank through the very delicate crux at the 2nd bolt. Fun face moves lead to a roof. Pull the roof and run it out to the anchors on 5.6 terrain. Optional medium cam in the run-out.

Look for a roof with a bolt. This route is right of Crazy yahoos and left of Gomez, Lopez, Fitzgerald
bolts, optional medium cam at the top

Start in the corner on easy terrain leading you to a 2 bolt technical crux. Pull the crux to finish on the same anchor as La mére à Luc pis des Burritos. Right of the obvious arête Macguffin in the corner. 7 bolts
Bolted anchor

This crag is situated in the industrial city of Saint John. Although, this doesn't sound appealing, the crag is nestled in an old limestone quarry in a peaceful residential neighbourhood. Despite being a decommissioned quarry, the rock is very solid as no explosives were used when it was exploited over a century ago. 
 This place collects sun, and dries out much more quickly than you'd expect. If the wind is blowing the right direction, it can be an excellent choice for early march / late november! That being said, sometimes the wind funnels in the quarry and it can be cold even in mid summer. 
  
 Please be courteous while visiting the area. The approach and the cliffs are on private property and the climbing here is tolerated. One confrontation with the owners or the neighbours and the privilege of climbing here could be lost.
